Cytologic diagnosis of leukemia and lymphoma. Values and limitations.
 The value and limitations of the cytologic diagnosis of lymphoma and leukemia using a multiparameter approach, including cytomorphology, immunocytochemistry, and flow cytometry, are discussed.
 Using these diagnostic modalities, most subtypes of lymphoma and leukemia can be classified accurately.
 The differential diagnoses of the different disease entities also are presented.
